                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13943814" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 01:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(I would prefer to leave the default of snapshot the same on both windows and linux, which means we should log a warning and ignore the flag instead of failing the operation.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945305" author="jmckenzie" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 16:26:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Went with protection in the startup .bat file to force addition of -par on repair if it&apos;s not there and log to stdout.  Lighter touch and isolates changes to windows environment only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945308" author="jmckenzie" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 16:27:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed ticket # listed in comment&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945315" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 16:30:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t addressing in code be more robust for invocations via jmx as well as .bat?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945329" author="jmckenzie" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 16:41:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would be more robust, yes, but also represent more invasive changes for temporary OS-specific workarounds.  If we want to err on the side of robustness that should be a trivial change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945357" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 17:05:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s go ahead and do that, we can just leave it out of 3.0 when we merge so there&apos;s no need to worry about it outliving its usefulness.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945419" author="jmckenzie" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 17:55:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;new patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13948013" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 15:41:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
